 j, and convolution covariance functions Cii(x,y) := (gi * gi)(x-y), vanishing for |x - y| &gt; di + dj and |x - y| &gt; 2di, respectively, Additional covariance functions on R3 are constructed using convolutions over the real numbers R, rather than R3. Families of compactly supported approximants to standard second- and third-order autoregressive functions are constructed as illustrative examples. Compactly supported covariance functions of the form C(x,y) := Co(|x - y|), x,y isin R3, where the functions Co(r) for r isin R are 5th-order piecewise rational functions, are also constructed. These functions are used to develop space-limited product covariance functions B(x, y) C(x, y), x, y isin S2, approximating given covariance functions B(x, y) supported on all of S2 × S2.},
